dot("$(1,0)$", (1,0), SW, fontsize(10));
dot("$(0,2)$", (0,2), NE, fontsize(10));
[/asy] ||| We start with the equations from the roots. From the point $(-1,0)$, we have $0 = f(-1) = -a - b + c + d$.  From the point $(1,0)$, we find $0 = f(1) = a - b + c + d$.  Solving these gives us $b + d = 0$, and thus if we substitute $d = 2$, we get $b + 2 = 0$. So, $b = -2$. However, I think I miscalculated $d$ as 2, when it should be 1. Redoing gives us $b = -1$.\  oxed{-1}

